        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 3:57PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 356 PM CDT/256 PM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm 10 miles southwest of Shields, or 25 miles north of
Bullhead, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Standing Rock and Standing Rock Nation.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
